                                "byte_start": 90021,
                                "byte_stop": 128473,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has the opinion of the court in case 06-562, United States versus Atlantic Research Corporation."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.587,
                        "stop": 243.383,
                        "byte_start": 128473,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.587,
                                "stop": 16.169,
                                "byte_start": 128473,
                                "byte_stop": 154700,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on the writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.169,
                                "stop": 25.574,
                                "byte_start": 154700,
                                "byte_stop": 192421,
                                "text": "Respondent Atlantic Research leads the facility where it retrofitted rocket motors for petitioner the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.574,
                                "stop": 31.832,
                                "byte_start": 192421,
                                "byte_stop": 217394,
                                "text": "The retrofitting process resulted in contamination of the facility."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.832,
                                "stop": 45.93,
                                "byte_start": 217394,
                                "byte_stop": 273819,
                                "text": "Under the Comprehensive Environmental Response Compensation and Liability Act (CERCLA), both Atlantic Research and the United States are potentially responsible for the contamination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.93,
                                "stop": 62.123,
                                "byte_start": 273819,
                                "byte_stop": 338602,
                                "text": "After Atlantic Research voluntarily cleaned up the site it sought to recover some of its expenses from the United States by filing suit under CERCLA Sections 107(a) and 113(f)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.123,
                                "stop": 76.56,
                                "byte_start": 338602,
                                "byte_stop": 396281,
                                "text": "After Atlantic Research filed suit we decided Cooper Industries versus Aviall Services, which foreclose Atlantic Research\u2019s Section 113(f) claim for contribution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.56,
                                "stop": 91.894,
                                "byte_start": 396281,
                                "byte_stop": 457616,
                                "text": "The District Court then dismissed Atlantic Research\u2019s 107(a) claim but the Court of Appeals reversed and held that Section 107(a) permitted one potentially responsible party sue another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.894,
                                "stop": 99.328,
                                "byte_start": 457616,
                                "byte_stop": 487396,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today we affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.328,
                                "stop": 112.294,
                                "byte_start": 487396,
                                "byte_stop": 539223,
                                "text": "CERCLA Section 107(a) defines four categories of persons as potentially responsible parties and makes those persons liable for certain contamination cause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.294,
                                "stop": 117.922,
                                "byte_start": 539223,
                                "byte_stop": 561792,
                                "text": "CERCLA also authorizes two causes for the actions for private parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.922,
                                "stop": 131.134,
                                "byte_start": 561792,
                                "byte_stop": 614560,
                                "text": "In Section 107(a), that permits cost recovery by certain parties and Section 113(f) it permits liable parties to seek contribution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.134,
                                "stop": 140.908,
                                "byte_start": 614560,
                                "byte_stop": 653743,
                                "text": "The dispute here seen is on what person subparagraph (B) of Section 107(a) permits to seek cost recovery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.908,
                                "stop": 148.226,
                                "byte_start": 653743,
                                "byte_stop": 683001,
                                "text": "The text of subparagraph (B) allows suits by \u201cany other person.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.226,
                                "stop": 160.348,
                                "byte_start": 683001,
                                "byte_stop": 731484,
                                "text": "In our view the phrase \u201cany other person\u201d in subparagraph (B) can be understood only with reference to the immediately preceding subparagraph."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.348,
                                "stop": 184.504,
                                "byte_start": 731484,
                                "byte_stop": 828137,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we hold that the phrase \u201cany other person\u201d refers to persons other than those listed in the preceding subparagraph because this preceding subparagraph list only the United States or State or an Indian tribe all persons other than those three may sue under subparagraph (B)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.504,
                                "stop": 195.229,
                                "byte_start": 828137,
                                "byte_stop": 870978,
                                "text": "Atlantic Research therefore qualifies as any other person and may recover its cost under the plain language of subparagraph (B)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.229,
                                "stop": 210.485,
                                "byte_start": 870978,
                                "byte_stop": 932000,
                                "text": "Contrary to the government\u2019s arguments this interpretation of Section 107(a) will not unduly conflict with Section 113(f)\u2019s cause of action for contribution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.485,
                                "stop": 221.632,
                                "byte_start": 932000,
                                "byte_stop": 976617,
                                "text": "The two provisions authorized clearly distinct remedies and provide causes of actions to persons in different procedural circumstances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 221.632,
                                "stop": 231.821,
                                "byte_start": 976617,
                                "byte_stop": 1017368,
                                "text": "Accordingly, Section 107(a) does not swallow the remedy provided by Section 113(f)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.821,
                                "stop": 240.484,
                                "byte_start": 1017368,
                                "byte_stop": 1052059,
                                "text": "Nor does today\u2019s decision undermine the settlement bar provided in Section 113(f)(2)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.484,
                                "stop": 243.383,
                                "byte_start": 1052059,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
